claims.text:
An organic compound represented by Formula (I):

[Formula (I)]

wherein, in Formula (I):
the compound comprises a 3,3'-bicarbazole core in which two carbazolyl units are bonded at the 3-position of each carbazolyl unit;
N₁ of a first carbazolyl unit is bonded to a group Ar₁;
N₂ of a second carbazolyl unit is bonded to a group Ar₂;
Ar₁ is selected from the group consisting of a substituted or unsubstituted C₆-C₃₀ aryl group and a substituted or unsubstituted C₂-C₃₀ heteroaryl group containing at least one heteroatom selected from N, O, and S;
Ar₂ is selected from the group consisting of phenyl, naphthyl, biphenylyl, and pyridinyl;
each of R₁, R₂, R₃, and R₄ is independently selected from the group consisting of hydrogen, deuterium, a C₁-C₁₂ linear or branched alkyl group, a C₆-C₁₈ aryl group, a C₂-C₁₈ heteroaryl group, a C₁-C₆ alkoxy group, and a halogen;
m is an integer from 0 to 4, representing the number of R₁ substituents on Ar₁;
n is an integer from 0 to 2, representing the number of R₂ substituents on Ar₂;
p is an integer from 0 to 4, representing the number of R₃ substituents on the first carbazolyl unit; and
q is an integer from 0 to 4, representing the number of R₄ substituents on the second carbazolyl unit.

An organic light-emitting device comprising:
an anode;
a cathode disposed opposite to the anode;
and an organic layer stack disposed between the anode and the cathode, the organic layer stack comprising:
a hole injection layer disposed on the anode;
a hole transport layer disposed on the hole injection layer;
an emitting layer disposed on the hole transport layer, the emitting layer comprising a host material and a dopant material, wherein the host material comprises the organic compound according to claim 1;
an electron transport layer disposed on the emitting layer; and
an electron injection layer disposed between the electron transport layer and the cathode.

A method for fabricating an organic light-emitting device, the method comprising:
(a) providing a substrate having an anode formed thereon;
(b) forming a hole injection layer on the anode by vacuum thermal evaporation at a deposition rate of 0.5 to 2.0 Å/s;
(c) forming a hole transport layer on the hole injection layer by vacuum thermal evaporation;
(d) co-depositing a host material and a dopant material on the hole transport layer to form an emitting layer, wherein the host material comprises the organic compound according to claim 1, the co-deposition is performed at a substrate temperature of 20°C to 80°C, and the emitting layer has a thickness of 10 nm to 60 nm;
(e) forming an electron transport layer on the emitting layer by vacuum thermal evaporation; and
(f) forming a cathode on the electron transport layer.

The organic compound according to claim 1, wherein the compound is selected from the group consisting of:
Compound 1: 9-(dibenzofuran-4-yl)-9'-phenyl-9H,9'H-3,3'-bicarbazole;
Compound 2: 9-(dibenzothiophen-4-yl)-9'-phenyl-9H,9'H-3,3'-bicarbazole;
Compound 3: 9-(biphenyl-4-yl)-9'-(pyridin-3-yl)-9H,9'H-3,3'-bicarbazole;
Compound 4: 9-(2-naphthyl)-9'-phenyl-6-tert-butyl-9H,9'H-3,3'-bicarbazole; and
Compound 5: 9-phenyl-9'-(9,9-dimethylfluoren-2-yl)-9H,9'H-3,3'-bicarbazole.
